oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector.hierarchy

Interface HierarchyInfo

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DynaAdminHierarchyInfo

    public interface HierarchyInfo
    Represents a hierarchical catalog. An implementation of this interface is expected to perform the following functions: -Provide the number of hierarchy levels and a way to identify each level. -Provide content such as id and spatial information of each record in a certain hierarchical level. -Provide hierarchical relations between records in different levels such as parent-child associations. The paths of the different hierarchical catalogs are specified at runtime by calling the load() method. It is discouraged to link the implementation with a fixed path. Instead, only the content specified by the load() method should be loaded.
    Author:
    hsaucedo

      • load

        void load(Path[] hierDataPaths,
          int fromLevel,
          JobConf conf)
   throws java.lang.Exception
        Loads the hierarchical catalog content from the given paths.
        Parameters:
        hierDataPaths - an array containing paths for each hierarchy level that needs to be loaded. The hierarchy levels to be loaded are determined by the paths array length and the value of fromLevel parameter. The array's length is inside the range: 1 <= length <= number of hierarchies. The paths are ordered by its hierarchy level in ascending way. The path in the array corresponds to the hierarchy level number resulting of adding the element index to the value of the fromLevel parameter (i + fromLevel). For example: for a hierarchy with 10 levels, load from level 6 to 10. In this case, the path array will contain 5 elements and fromValue will be 6. If the 10 levels need to be loaded, the path array length must be 10 and fromValue must be 1.
        fromLevel - specifies the hierarchy level from which the hierarchy levels must be loaded. The value is in the range 1<= fromLevel <= number of hierarchies.
        conf - the job configuration
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • loadFromIndex

        void loadFromIndex(HierarchyDataIndexReader[] readers,
                   int fromLevel,
                   Configuration conf)
            throws java.lang.Exception
        Loads the hierarchical catalog content from previously generated indices. As with the load() method, the number and hierarchies loaded as the top hierarchy level loaded depends on the length of the readers array parameter and the value of the fromLevel parameter.
        Parameters:
        readers - an array of HierarchyDataIndexReader. The readers are sorted by hierarchy level in ascending order. The top hierarchy level is determined by the value of fromLevel.
        fromLevel - specifies the hierarchy level from which the hierarchy levels must be loaded. The value is in the range 1<= fromLevel <= number of hierarchies.
        conf - the job configuration
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
